Subject: [PATCH] feat: hide Missiles pref control, add saved-build switcher on
 Fitting screen
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Missiles auto/prefer/avoid control:
- Hidden behind a SHOW_MISSILE_PREF = false flag (FittingScreen.tsx),
  not deleted — marked as a removal candidate pending a decision on
  whether missile loadouts stay in the planner long-term. All
  underlying logic and state (missilePref, applyRole's missile-pref
  handling) is untouched, so flipping the flag back to true fully
  restores it.

Saved-build switcher:
- New 'Load saved build…' dropdown in the fit-actions bar, grouped
  into 'For this ship' and 'Other ships' (showing the ship name for
  the latter, since it's picking a starting point on a different hull).
  Only renders when at least one build is saved.
- Selecting an entry reuses the same sanitize-against-current-slots
  logic Saved page's 'Open' button already used — refactored into a
  shared openBuild() helper in App.tsx (was inlined in the SavedView
  onOpen handler) and passed to FittingScreen as onSwitchBuild.
- Verified end-to-end: same-ship switch keeps the screen on that ship
  and swaps the loadout in place; cross-ship switch navigates to the
  other ship with that build's loadout applied.
